name: o-methyl carbamate
Reason: 1,3-dioxolane has a melting point of around 40 degrees Celsius. The methoxy group introduces additional molecular weight and van der Waals interactions, raising the melting point by about +5 degrees Celsius. The carbamate group introduces additional rigid structures that can participate in dipole interactions and potentially hydrogen bonding, further raising the melting point by about +10 degrees Celsius.
